<span id="freeTextContainer4390420883390723769">Dark and grittier than the Black Company. Mage Blood is an entertaining media-res introduction to Tempus, the Riddler, Niko, and the Sacred Band of Stepsons, characters created by Janet and Chris Morris.<br/><br/>Filled with an ancient pantheon of deities as found in Greco-Roman times, archmages of nearly godlike power, and the nations that serve as their pawns, Mage Blood delivers a raw look at what warcraft might have been under such conditions in ancient times.<br/><br/>For those who like the realism, the no-hol</span>
  <span id="freeText4390420883390723769" style="display:none">Dark and grittier than the Black Company. Mage Blood is an entertaining media-res introduction to Tempus, the Riddler, Niko, and the Sacred Band of Stepsons, characters created by Janet and Chris Morris.<br /><br />Filled with an ancient pantheon of deities as found in Greco-Roman times, archmages of nearly godlike power, and the nations that serve as their pawns, Mage Blood delivers a raw look at what warcraft might have been under such conditions in ancient times.<br /><br />For those who like the realism, the no-holds-barred look at warring nations and the insatiable appetites of wizards with too much power and little able to withstand it, I recommend delving in to the Sacred Band series. Mage Blood is an excellent place to start.<br /><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/5767415.Ernie_Laurence_Jr_" title="Ernie Laurence Jr." rel="nofollow noopener">Ernie Laurence Jr.</a><br />Author of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13515165.Sundered__Islands_of_Loar___1_" title="Sundered (Islands of Loar, #1) by Ernie Laurence Jr." rel="nofollow noopener">Sundered</a></span>
